  "text": "Antibodies to topoisomerase II␣ and TT were assessed using an indirect ELISA method with recombinant proteins. Briefly, alternate columns on Immulon 4HBX plates (Dynex Technologies, Chantilly, VA) were coated overnight with purified human topoisomerase II␣ (Topogen, Columbus, OH) or TT antigen (Sigma Chemicals Inc, St. Louis, MO) and PBS/BSA, blocked for 1 hour with PBS/BSA, and washed with PBS/Tween. After washing, 50 L/well of control or experimental sera were added in duplicate titration sets. After overnight incubation at 4°C, plates were washed again and antihuman/HRP conjugate added 50 L/well. Plates were washed again after a 45-minute incubation at 4°C, and developed as previously described. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Seventy-five of 104 samples had sufficient remaining volume to test for immunity to topoisomerase II␣.",
